{"workData":{"description":"'There has been no such analysis of the corrupting power of the police state in Soviet literature'--Stuart Hood in the *Listener*

Solzhenitsyn, like Oleg Kostoglotov, the central character of this novel, went in the mid-1950s from concentration camp to cancer ward and later recovered. The British publication of *Cancer Ward* in 1968 confirmed him as Russia's greatest living novelist although it has never been openly published in the Soviet Union.","title":"Раковый корпус","first_sentence":{"type":"/type/text","value":"On top of everything, the cancer wing was Number 13."},"first_publish_date":"1968","key":"/works/OL258366W","authors":[{"author":{"key":"/authors/OL222507A"},"type":{"key":"/type/author_role"}}],"subject_times":["Fiction","Russia","Soviet Union","1955","1945-1991"],"subjects":["Russia","Soviet Union","Continental european fiction (fictional works by one author)","Soviet union, fiction","Patients","Cancer","Fiction","Political fiction","Slavic philology","Russian Fiction","Prisoners in Fiction","Social conditions","Psychological aspects","18.53 Russian literature"],"type":{"key":"/type/work"},"excerpts":[{"excerpt":"On top of everything, the cancer wing was Number 13."},{"pages":"282","excerpt":"Only a prisoner in his first years of sentence believes, every time he is summoned from his cell and told to collect his belongings, that he is being called to freedom. To him every whisper of an amnesty sounds like the trumpets of archangels. But they call him out of his cell, read his some loathsome documents and shove him in another cell on the floor below, even darker than the previous one but with the same stale, used-up air.","author":{"key":"/people/catzrfluffy"}}],"covers":[12709648,77468,10050704,8963031,419455,10737268,12393651],"subject_places":["Soviet Union","Uzbekistan"],"latest_revision":12,"revision":12,"created":{"type":"/type/datetime","value":"2009-10-24T00:36:36.861649"},"last_modified":{"type":"/type/datetime","value":"2022-04-07T04:58:24.619193"}},"authorData":{"type":{"key":"/type/author"},"alternate_names":["Aleksandr Isaevich Solzhenit͡s︡yn, Алекса́ндр Иса́евич Сол